title: Bug 110566 - Wrong data set result returned when setting an invalid filter expression for row[0]
description: When setting a filter expression like 'row[0] equals to 0', the system either returns an incorrect result set or just returns a null result set.
OB: The software does not return the expected data set. It either returns an incorrect result set or a null result set.
EB: The software should display a relevant error message when an invalid filter expression is set.
SR:
To reproduce the issue, follow these steps:
1. Set the filter expression 'row[0] equals to 0' for a data set.
2. Observe the result set returned by the system.
